name: microservice-architecture-java
description: A sample Java microservices architecture project using Docker, Spring Boot, and Spring Cloud. Demonstrates key patterns in distributed systems, including service discovery, API gateway, and centralized configuration.

name: flight-reservation-management-system
description: ✈️ A microservices-based flight reservation management system that handles booking, payment, user, flight, and notification services with a service registry for seamless inter-service communication.

name: Teacher_MS
description: A Teacher Management System Microsesrvice, responsible for communicating with a Student MS Microservice.

name: NTTDATA-CustomerMS
description: This microservice is part of a banking system that manages customer information. It allows creating, retrieving, updating, and deleting customer details such as name, surname, DNI (ID), and email. The service communicates with other microservices, like the Account Microservice, to provide an integrated banking management solution.

name: online-store
description: This directory contains all the microservices for the system, each focused on a specific domain or functionality, enabling a modular and scalable architecture.

name: SalesManagements-Spring-Cloud-
description: A sales management system built with microservices: Produit, Client, and Vente services, an API Gateway, and an Authentication microservice. It uses Consul for service discovery and Angular for the frontend. This architecture ensures scalability, modularity, and secure interactions via JWT authentication.

name: WandaSync
description: An e-commerce system based on the principles of Event-Driven Architecture (EDA) and microservices. It integrates highly relevant technologies like Kafka, Spring Boot, and MongoDB.

name: real-time-prediction
description: This project builds a real-time ML system to predict Bitcoin prices. It includes data pipelines for preprocessing, model training with XGBoost, and real-time prediction deployment using REST APIs and cloud services. The system is modular, scalable, and built with microservices for efficient performance.

name: api-gateway
description: A high-performance API Gateway written in Go, following Clean Architecture principles. Features dynamic routing, middleware support, and plugin system for extensibility. Built for reliability and ease of use in modern microservices architectures.

name: Service-Routing-Gateway
description: This repository contains the API Gateway for the School Management System, built using Spring Cloud Gateway. It serves as a single entry point, routing requests to microservices such as the Student and School services. The gateway leverages Eureka for service discovery, enabling dynamic routing and seamless integration between services
